# trading mind map 

from a trader’s perspective.  
Structured it hierarchically so one can visualize all core concepts,   
their relationships, and how they affect decisions.   
This is exactly how pros think when analyzing a market.  


🌐 Ultimate Trading Mind Map (Trader View)
1️⃣ Market Fundamentals

    Assets / Instruments
        Crypto (BTC, ETH, SOL…)
        Forex (EUR/USD…)
        Stocks (AAPL, TSLA…)
        Derivatives (Futures, Options, CFDs, KOs)
    Market Types
        Spot
        Futures / Margin
        Options
        Derivatives

2️⃣ Price Mechanics

    Bid / Ask → best buy vs best sell
    Spread → Ask − Bid (cost of immediate execution)
    Last price / Close price → recent trade
    High / Low / Open / Close (OHLC)
    Liquidity → ease of buying/selling
    Volatility → magnitude of price fluctuations

3️⃣ Orders & Execution

    Market order → execute now, pay spread
    Limit order → set price, avoid spread
    Stop order → trigger market order at price
    Stop-limit order → trigger limit order at price
    Trailing stop → dynamic stop-loss following price
    Take-profit order → lock profits automatically
    OCO / Bracket orders → advanced conditional setups

4️⃣ Costs of Trading

    Spread → unavoidable in market orders
    Slippage → difference between expected and execution price
    Fees / Commissions → exchange cost
    Overnight / Financing fees → leveraged positions
    Taxes → jurisdiction-dependent

5️⃣ Risk & Position Management

    Leverage / Margin → amplify positions
    Margin call → additional collateral needed
    Liquidation → forced close to prevent negative balance
    Position sizing → controlling exposure
    Drawdown → max capital loss
    PnL (Profit & Loss) → realized vs unrealized

6️⃣ Trading Strategies

    Scalping → very short-term, small gains
    Day trading → intraday, no overnight positions
    Swing trading → multi-day positions
    Position trading → long-term holding
    Hedging → reduce exposure
    Arbitrage → exploit price differences across markets

7️⃣ Market Analysis

    Technical Analysis
        Candlestick patterns
        Support / Resistance
        Trend / Momentum
        Indicators (RSI, MACD, EMA, SMA…)
        Volatility measures (ATR, Bollinger Bands…)
    Fundamental Analysis
        News / Macro events
        Earnings reports / Financials
        Regulatory news / Crypto events
    Sentiment Analysis
        Social media / market sentiment
        Fear & Greed index

8️⃣ Execution Environment (Trader’s Reality)

    Order book depth → see liquidity at each level
    Market impact → large orders move price
    Latency / Speed → faster execution = better fills
    Slippage monitoring → track real execution cost
    Spread awareness → avoid wide spreads

9️⃣ Trading Psychology & Discipline

    Risk-reward ratio → planned vs potential
    Stop-loss discipline → avoid emotional decisions
    Trade journal → record entries, exits, mistakes
    Overtrading → avoid due to fatigue
    Patience / Timing → wait for setups, don’t chase

🔀 Interconnections (key for decision-making)

    Spread + Slippage → impacts profits for scalping
    Liquidity + Volatility → influences risk for all strategies
    Leverage + Margin → affects liquidation risk
    Technical indicators → trigger limit/market orders
    Fundamental news → triggers volatility spikes → slippage

💡 Trader’s Mindset Summary

    Always think in cost & risk terms first: Spread, Slippage, Fees, Volatility
    Execution matters more than analysis: Market vs Limit order, position size
    Discipline > Strategy: Stop-loss, patience, risk/reward
    Liquidity & time frame = your best friend for day trading/scalping

